HEADWORD: Scrine
<hw>Scrine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>scrinium</ets>
a case for books, letters, etc.: cf. OF. <ets>escrin</ets>, F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧crin</ets>. See <er>Shrine</er>.]</ety> <def>A chest,
bookcase, or other place, where writings or curiosities are deposited; a
shrine.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>But laid them up in immortal <qex>scrine</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scringe</ent>⟦br⟧
